<subSubSection id="D694C5B9AB5DFFBA00DCF975FD05F8E8" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph id="9E319632AB5DFFBA00DCF975FD05F8E8" blockId="3.[151,1437,1688,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5DFFBA00DCF975FEA8F93C" bold="true" box="[151,344,1688,1714]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Male terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5DFFBA0122F975FE04F93D" box="[361,500,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
). Tegmen length about 2.0 mm; lateral lobes rather straightly tapered from middle to narrowly rounded apices, each about 0.4 mm long and 0.2 mm wide; median lobe plus median struts slightly curved, slightly longer than tegmen in length; median struts shorter than half of whole median lobe in length; apex of ventral plate strongly projected (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5DFFBA0263F8E9FD79F891" box="[552,649,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Fig. 15a</figureCitation>
); median foramen elongate; internal sac with 2 hook-shaped sclerites (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5DFFBA00D4F8C5FEB3F8CD" box="[159,323,1832,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Figs. 15b, 15c</figureCitation>
). Tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5DFFBA01A0F8C5FD50F8CC" box="[491,672,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Figs. 14a &amp; 14c</figureCitation>
) trapezoidal, apex slightly emarginated with round angles, provided with medium long setae along apical and lateral sides.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D694C5B9AB5DFFBC008CF89DFB7DFF5B" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9E319632AB5DFFBC008CF89DFB7DFF5B" blockId="3.[151,1437,1688,2003]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5DFFBA008CF89DFEB2F804" bold="true" box="[199,322,1904,1930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is mostly similar to 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5DFFBA02FDF89DFC0CF804" authority="(Gressitt, 1942)" baseAuthorityName="Gressitt" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[694,1020,1904,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anaches" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albaninus">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5DFFBA02FDF89DFCB3F804" box="[694,835,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">A. albaninus</emphasis>
(Gressitt, 1942)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily distinguished from it by the following features: the whitish band more oblique; the anterior margins of the whitish bands “U”-shaped, instead of slightly oblique line; the sexual patches on sternite IV closer to each other (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5DFFBA040DF855FB17F85D" box="[1094,1255,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1929,1953]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,937,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-235@5.[151,1436,930,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Anaches spp., ♂♂, ventral view, showing the sexual patch on sternite IV. 9. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 10. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 11. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942). a. Abdomen, dry specimens before dissection; b. Ventral view of the sternites III &amp; IV, after dissection. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521522/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Figs. 10a, 10b</figureCitation>
), instead of well separated (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5BFFBC0144FF7AFE5EFF3C" box="[271,430,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1929,1953]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,937,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-235@5.[151,1436,930,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Anaches spp., ♂♂, ventral view, showing the sexual patch on sternite IV. 9. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 10. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 11. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942). a. Abdomen, dry specimens before dissection; b. Ventral view of the sternites III &amp; IV, after dissection. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521522/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Figs. 11a, 11b</figureCitation>
); the apex of tergite VIII emarginated (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5BFFBC0314FF7AFC0DFF3F" box="[863,1021,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Figs. 14a, 14c</figureCitation>
), instead of rounded (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5BFFBC04A4FF7AFA7FFF3C" box="[1263,1423,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Figs. 16a, 16c</figureCitation>
); the apex of ventral plate of median lobe projected (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5BFFBC0298FF56FCC2FF5B" box="[723,818,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Fig. 15a</figureCitation>
), instead of pointed (
<figureCitation id="06B58AB7AB5BFFBC0454FF56FB8FFF5B" box="[1055,1151,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,826,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-254@6.[151,1436,813,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Anaches spp., ♂♂. 12–13. A. m-signatus sp. nov.; 14-15. A. yitingi Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013; 16–17. A. albaninus (Gressitt, 1942); 12, 14, 16. Tergite VIII with sternites VIII &amp; IX; 13, 15, 17. median lobe &amp; tegmen. a. ventral view. b. lateral view; c. dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.05 mm or 1 mm, some not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521524/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Fig. 17a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
